label: SignalDescriptor
comment: The signal descriptor that has a terminal.

label: DetailedModelTypeDynamics
comment: The detailed model type dynamics that has detailed model descriptor.

label: FunctionDescriptor
comment: The functional descriptor that has equation descriptor artifact.

label: equationLanguageKind
comment: Describes what kind of language is used to describe the equation.

label: equationLanguageTypeOther
comment: Defines the language used to describe equations.

label: DetailedModelDescriptor
comment: The detailed model descriptor that is part of the detailed model type dynamics.

label: SignalDescriptor
comment: The signal which relates to this dynamics function block.

label: EquationDescriptorArtifact
comment: The equation descriptor artifact for this function descriptor.

label: InputOutputDescriptor
comment: The input and output descriptor of this function descriptor.

label: LowerLimit
comment: The lower limit of the limiter descriptor.

label: ParameterDescriptor
comment: The parameter descriptor for this function descriptor.

label: UpperLimit
comment: The upper limit of the limiter descriptor.

label: describedByArtifact
comment: Identifies if the function descriptor is described by an artifact. If true, the function is described by an artifact. If false the equation shall be described by the attribute equation.

label: equation
comment: Mathematical expression of the function in the specified language. A function can be e.g. first-order lag element, more complex transfer function, etc.

label: equationLanguageKind
comment: Describes what kind of language is used to describe the equation.

label: initialConditionsEquation
comment: Mathematical expression (in the specified language) of the initial conditions of the function descriptor.

label: description
comment: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: name
comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

label: FunctionDescriptor
comment: The function descriptor that has this input and output descriptor.

label: InputSignal
comment: The input signal for this input descriptor.

label: LimiterDescriptor
comment: The limiter descriptor that has input and output descriptor.

label: OperatorDescriptor
comment: The operator descriptor that has input and output descriptor.

label: OutputSignal
comment: The output signal for this output descriptor.

label: InputOutputDescriptor
comment: The input and output descriptor that belongs to the limiter descriptor.

label: LowerLimitFunction
comment: The function fo the lower limit.

label: UpperLimitFunction
comment: The function for the upper limit.

label: InputOutputDescriptor
comment: The input and otput descriptor that belongs to the  operator descriptor.

label: logicalKind
comment: Logical kind of the operator. Used only if operatorKind is set to OperatorDescriptorKind.logical.

label: operatorKind
comment: Kinds of operator.

label: FunctionDescriptor
comment: The function descriptor that has parameter descriptor.

label: constraintKind
comment: The kind for the constraint.

label: constraintValue
comment: The value of the constraint. Used in all cases except when constraint kind is "custom".

label: engineeringUnit
comment: The engineering unit of the value.

label: kind
comment: The kind of the parameter.

label: referenceCustomConstraint
comment: Provides the reference to a custom constraint related to this parameter. It is used for more complex constraints that are not possible to express by attributes constraintKind and constraintValue. The reference is and IRI to a description of the constraint that conform to specific language for describing constraints, e.g. SHACL.

label: sequenceNumber
comment: Sequence number of the parameter among the set of parameters associated with the related proprietary user-defined model.

label: typicalValue
comment: Typical value for the parameter. The datatype is as specified in attribute valueXSDdatatype.

label: typicalValueRangeMax
comment: Maximum value (upper end of the range) of the typical range.

label: typicalValueRangeMin
comment: Minimum value (lower end of the range) of the typical range.

label: valueXSDdatatype
comment: The XSD datatype of the value.

label: ACDCTerminal
comment: Th eterminal for this signal descriptor.

label: DynamicsFunctionBlock
comment: The dynamics function block to which this signal belongs to.

label: InputDescriptor
comment: The input of the input descriptor that has this signal descriptor.

label: OutputDescriptor
comment: The output of this input and output desciptor that has a signal descriptor.

label: isSignalInverted
comment: Indicates if the signal is inverted. True means the signal is inverted, i.e. multiplied by -1. False means the signal is not inverted.
